I agree with @garrettginner . Obviously, it’s an over crook, but it was called a nosegrind by mainstream skate culture, every overcrook in thrasher magazine would be labeled “nosegrind”. When pros would talk about the trick, they would call it nosegrind, every sponsored skater I knew, referred to this “overcrooks” as nosegrinds. This is just what it was called, for the same reason a lot of tricks have names that make little to know sense (don’t even get me started with the ridiculousness of fakie tricks). But the next generation is calling them overcrooks, so now I am too. I don’t have pride in trick names, I just want to be able to translate the trick I’m doing, fastest to whoever I’m talking to lol

I MOVED BACK TO LA!  New video, link in bio 💛 Been a long time coming, I love being in California. It was the first home I chose, probably the first place where I found people who I felt saw the world the way I did. New York was an incredible detour, Texas with @saradietschy family was perfect for uncertain Covid times, but LA is the only place i want to be at post Covid.  I’m hungrier than ever to do my job in the most entertaining way I can. Im a sign off before I accidentally get too cheesy but this is a big moment, i can’t wait to live in la with my wife, and make all the videos I’ve dreamed of. No more imposter syndrome, no more waiting, I’m going at this thing with everything I’ve got 👊

Thought I was gonna move to la, and skate even more; perfect weather, all my friends, TONS of parks and spots, but… im getting bit with the art bug again. Obviously I can do both, but I’m finding myself WAY more attracted to the other opportunities a place like LA provides, seeing places like universal, Disney, Warner bros, while out on a casual stroll, has me wanting to shoot for bigger dreams. Crazy how much a different location can switch your perspective. Here’s to getting out of our own way 🍻

Learned 5 flips off of stuff, but it’s a bit of bittersweet news /: I’ve been getting HEAVILY back into skateboarding, and over the last 2 years or so, most of the injuries I’ve sustained are from parkour 😅 it’s obviously cause I’ve been pushing a little too quickly, but basically, I’m still going to do it, but I need to slow down the progression a lot more if I want to be able to keep progressing in skating and making videos I’m proud of. Such SUCH a fun…. Sport? Love the community, looking forward to growing, just always a little disappointed when I have to scale back on progression 🥲

There’s an infinite supply of clips from @kechaud life to choose from. No one could skate like him. From seeing him on tv skating a Dew Tour, to skating with him when I first moved to California, to filming him for a YouTube video, and to be able to sponsor him for a contest, I’m unbelievably blessed to have met such an incredibly cool, collected, nice beast of a human and skateboarder. Today has felt unreal, for a lot of us. There are no words that can prevent the hurt and frustration that anyone who knew Kechaud feels. He made people happy, and he pursued what made him happy. Rest easy homie 💛
